00147 
00148   count is the actual size of the buffer for the string

00215 /* NC variable: description and data */
00216 typedef struct {
00217     NC_string *name ;
00218     NC_iarray *assoc ; /* user definition */

00220     unsigned long *dsizes ; /* compiled info */

00222     nc_type type ;      /* the discriminant */
00223     unsigned long len ;     /* the total length originally allocated */
00224     size_t szof ;       /* sizeof each value */

00226 #ifdef HDF
00227     NC *cdf;    /* handle of the file where this var belongs to  */
00228     int32 vgid; /* id of the variable's Vgroup */
00229     uint16 data_ref;    /* ref of the variable's data storage (if exists) */
00230     uint16 data_tag;    /* tag of the variable's data storage (if exists) */
00231     uint16 ndg_ref;     /* ref of ndg for this dataset */
00232     hdf_vartype_t var_type; /* IS_SDSVAR == is an SDS variable 
00233                    IS_CRDVAR == is a coordinate variable 
00234                    UNKNOWN == because the var was created prior to
00235                     this distinction */
00236     intn   data_offset; /* non-traditional data may not begin at 0 */
00237     int32  block_size;  /* size of the blocks for unlimited dim. datasets */
00238     int numrecs;    /* number of records this has been filled to */
00239     int32 aid;  /* aid for DFTAG_SD data */
00240     int32 HDFtype;  /* type of this variable as HDF thinks */
00241     int32 HDFsize;  /* size of this variable as HDF thinks */
00242     /* These next two flags control when space in the file is allocated
00243         for a new dataset.  They are used (currently) in SDwritedata() and
00244         hdf_get_vp_aid() to allocate the full length of a new fixed-size dataset
00245         which is not writing fill values, instead of letting them get created
00246         as an "appendable" dataset and probably get converted into a linked-
00247         block special element when they don't need to be one */
00248     int32   created;    /* BOOLEAN == is newly created */
00249     int32   set_length; /* BOOLEAN == needs length set */
00250     int32   is_ragged;  /* BOOLEAN == is a ragged array */
00251     int32 * rag_list;   /* size of ragged array lines */
00252     int32   rag_fill;   /* last line in rag_list to be set */
00253     vix_t * vixHead;    /* list of VXR records for CDF data storage */
00254 #endif
00255 } NC_var ;
